H0.text: Which World War II Aircraft was known as the 'Flying Stringbag'. Fairey Swordfish

H1.text: Which World War II Aircraft was known as the 'Flying Stringbag'. Supermarine Walrus

H2.text: Which World War II Aircraft was known as the 'Flying Stringbag'. Vought F4U Corsair

H3.text: Which World War II Aircraft was known as the 'Flying Stringbag'. Stringbag

A4.text: The Fairey Swordfish was nicknamed 'Stringbag' due to the variety of stores and equipment it could carry.

A5.text: The nickname 'Stringbag' was not due to the aircraft's structural complexity but its versatility in carrying equipment.
